# WiseResume — Windsurf Agent Rules

Before any UI, styling, animation, or component work, read:
- `DESIGN.md` — visual design system (color, type, components, motion, Do's/Don'ts)
- `PRODUCT.md` — strategic context (register: product UI, brand, anti-references, principles)

## Non-negotiable constraints

**Color**
- Landing page: always use `var(--lp-eyebrow)` / `var(--lp-brand)` tokens, never hardcode `#9E1B22` or `#1D4ED8` in landing components
- Neutrals lean cool — `#F7F7F8` yes, `#FAF7F2` never
- No gradient text, no warm/beige/cream backgrounds

**Motion**
- No `type: 'spring'` anywhere — in props or variant objects
- Canonical ease-out-quart: `[0.22, 1, 0.36, 1]` — in variants: cast as `[number, number, number, number]`
- Button duration: `0.18s`. Section reveal duration: `0.45s`
- All JS animation loops (`setInterval`/`setTimeout`/`rAF`) gated on `useReducedMotion()` from `framer-motion`
- Reduced motion → stop loop + skip to final state + `initial={false}` not `initial={{}}`

**Accessibility**
- Focus ring on every interactive element — never remove
- 44px minimum touch target
- Font size floor: 0.72rem semantic, 0.68rem decorative

**Anti-patterns (refuse)**
- `border-left` colored stripe on cards
- `z-index: 999/9999`
- Identical card grids
- Content gated behind animation triggers

## After editing UI files
The design detector runs automatically via `.claude/settings.json` PostToolUse hook.
To run manually: `node .claude/skills/impeccable/scripts/detect.mjs --json <files>`
Address all findings before marking work complete.
